The optical experiments were performed using a Woollam variable angle spectroscopic ellipsometer (VASE) system. Measurements were carried out as a function of photon energy in the range 0.75–4.5 eV with an energy step size of 0.1 eV; this corresponds to a wavelength range of 275–1650 nm. Spectra were obtained at incident angles in the range 45–75° with respect to the surface normal. In reflection ellipsometry, the change in the polarization state of light with a well-defined polarization upon reflection at an interface is measured. The complex reflection coefficient ρ is defined as1ρ=rprs=tanΨexpiΔ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
